  "response_text": "A glamorous, fair-skinned woman with short, voluminous copper-blonde hair sits in a dim dressing-room-like setting beside a mirror edged with round glowing bulbs. Dark greenery and pale flowers fill the background, giving the space a staged, theatrical feel. She wears a loose rust-brown robe or dress with a low neckline, earrings, and pronounced eye makeup. At first she is seen mainly through the mirror, touching the side of her neck or hair with one hand, then smiling broadly as she looks toward her reflection and the viewer. Her real profile appears at the left edge while her reflected face remains to the right. White on-screen text identifies her as “Juliet Prowse.” She turns away from the mirror, still smiling, and shifts forward and out of the seated pose.\n\nThe view changes to a close look at her legs stretched out horizontally against a dark background. She is wearing sheer pantyhose and delicate strappy high-heeled sandals. One leg rests above the other, with the ankle and lower calf clearly visible; the pantyhose lie smooth against the skin. Her hand hovers above and gestures near the ankle area, drawing attention to the fit around the ankle.\n\nShe then appears again from the waist up in the same dark, floral dressing-room setting. She looks down briefly, then lifts a small egg-shaped package beside her face. The package is white with a blue band and the Leggs name on it. Holding it upright in one hand, she presents it toward the viewer while speaking, smiling at moments and keeping the product near her cheek so the label is easy to see.\n\nA plain beige title card follows. In large red serif capital letters centered on the screen, it reads “MEMORY YARN.” Small copyright text appears at the lower left, including “© 1978 Leggs Products.” The words remain on screen for several moments, emphasizing the product feature named in the audio context.\n\nThe commercial ends with a product display against a dark background and pale floor. A large white Leggs egg package stands upright, the blue “Leggs” logo printed on the top half. The egg is open in the middle, with the top and bottom separated like a hinged container. Through the rectangular opening, a pair of smooth pantyhosed legs in strappy heels is visible, posed elegantly inside the package. The legs withdraw or disappear as the egg closes into a complete oval. The final image shows the closed white Leggs egg above black on-screen text reading, “Nothing beats a great pair of Leggs.”",
